import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='rate', hue='series', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rate across all industries?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    avg_unemployment_rate = data.groupby('series')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='series', y='rate', data=avg_unemployment_rate)
    plt.title('Which industry has the highest average unemployment rate?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Industry')
    plt.ylabel('Average Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Industry', loc='upper right', labels=avg_unemployment_rate['series'])
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.boxplot(x='month', y='rate', data=data)
    ax.set_title('How does the unemployment rate vary across different months?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Month')
    ax.set_ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
